    </StandardHierarchyLevel>
    <StatementCodes>
      <StatementCode>CCSS.Math.Content.7.RP.A.2c</StatementCode>
    </StatementCodes>
    <Statements>
      <Statement>Represent proportional relationships by equations. &lt;i&gt;For example, if total cost t is proportional to the number n of items purchased at a constant price p, the relationship between the total cost and the number of items can be expressed as t = pn&lt;/i&gt;.</Statement>
