      <Statement>Understand that multiplication is extended from fractions to rational numbers by requiring that operations continue to satisfy the properties of operations, particularly the distributive property, leading to products such as (&amp;ndash;1)(&amp;ndash;1) = 1 and the rules for multiplying signed numbers. Interpret products of rational numbers by describing real-world contexts.</Statement>
