    <StatementCodes>
      <StatementCode>CCSS.Math.Content.7.NS.A.2b</StatementCode>
    </StatementCodes>
    <Statements>
      <Statement>Understand that integers can be divided, provided that the divisor is not zero, and every quotient of integers (with non-zero divisor) is a rational number. If &lt;i&gt;p&lt;/i&gt; and &lt;i&gt;q&lt;/i&gt; are integers, then &amp;ndash;(&lt;i&gt;p&lt;/i&gt;/&lt;i&gt;q&lt;/i&gt;) = (&amp;ndash;&lt;i&gt;p&lt;/i&gt;)/&lt;i&gt;q&lt;/i&gt; = &lt;i&gt;p&lt;/i&gt;/(&amp;ndash;&lt;i&gt;q&lt;/i&gt;). Interpret quotients of rational numbers by describing real-world contexts.</Statement>
    </Statements>
